<sec>
<st>
Achievements</st>
<p>

The Monte Carlo project developed a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../783/5783.xml">
software program</link> used for <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../934/22934.xml">
probabilistic</link> modelling of chemical food intake. Data sets used to perform <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../354/2080354.xml">
probabilistic risk assessment</link>s were collected. The research results of the project enable European and US government agencies, universities and R&amp;D departments of food companies to use validated and peer-reviewed exposure models for food chemicals and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../575/66575.xml">
nutrients</link>.   </p>

